In SA, many home-owners have made money by providing short-term leasing of holiday cottages, apartments and houses. Before listing your property on platforms like Airbnb, however, you need to do sufficient research to find out if it’s legal for you to offer short-term rentals and how the income will be taxed. According to attorney Marlon Shevelew, Director at Marlon Shevelew & Associates Inc, short-term leasing models such as Airbnb pose legal challenges for those who own sectional-title properties where the conduct of owners and/or occupiers is regulated and governed by the scheme’s management and rules of conduct. 